video_title: Australia v India | WTC23 Final | Match Highlights
author: @saisuhas5316
text:
The players who are adored the most by many cricket fans across our country sadly are very weak when they play knockout matches. People might not like what I'm gonna say but India doesn't have a player who can lead the team well, do the required sacrifices and I mean it. Dhoni played the 2019 WC only as a hitter down the order which is alright for a 37 year old. Despite being 37 and not being able to perform in crucial matches, Rohit is still the opener and the captain of the team. BCCI unlike the Australian cricket board has no guts to take bold decisions and are bound to the cricket fans and their feelings. Only when they do something experimental, India can win an icc tournament. They also didn't do anything new about the t20 wc squad (2024). Rohit has the worst records and still he is the opener and captain. Its the same squad that failed many times in the past but with very minute changes. Guess what, Rahul who can play as an anchor isn't there. Ruturaj who has been extraordinary this ipl isnt there. Jaiswal who is out of form is in. Our bowling sucks, opening sucks. Kohli performs once in a bluemoon in knockouts and their fans still blabber about his knock vs Pak in 2022 which is useless. 
Indian fans are the dumbest and the team deserves this.
I don't mind Australia winning the T20 WC once again at all.

text: First time ever I actually watched ashes live last year before I just used to watch highlights and sometimes not even that. Before Ashes 2023 I used to think Pak vs India is the best rivalry in cricket and very competitive as well(In T20is) but after watching Ashes 2023, Pak vs India rivalry doesn't even come close to this rivalry, This is El Classico of cricket. That Cummins and Lyon partnership in 1st test, That Stokes 155, that Bairstow controversial stump out, That Lyon innings with injury, That Bairstow 99* to shut his haters, That Smith 100 after getting booed, that social media rivalry of British Media vs Aussies Media,  that trick/magic of bales from Broad, and who can forget that fairy tale ending of Broad's career. Literally the perfect rivalry. Ashes is the undisputed king of rivalries in cricket.

author: @Make_SL_Great_Again
text:
If this innings hadn't been played, Australia would have had to play a semi-final against India.
However, at that time, Australia was unaware of any alleged pitch-tampering by the Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI) or biased officiating. Therefore, it's impossible to say definitely whether they would have been beaten in the same way as New Zealand in that semi-final.
Regardless, if Glenn Maxwell hadn't played this innings, India's chances of winning the 2023 Cricket World Cup would have undoubtedly increased🥳

author: @classiccricketmatches152
text: Sorry, but this was not "one of the greatest" ODI knocks,.....it WAS the GREATEST ODI knock of all time, PERIOD! This is because it's the only ODI double hundred score to be scored lower than a opener or one-down batsman (he came in at 4-down), his team had basically collapsed to 91-7 with 201 runs needed from 189 balls, AND it is also the only double ODI hundred scored by a batsman during a chase under huge pressure, that too in a world cup game in an almost virtual knock-out situation, after which his team went on to win the World Cup. Don't think this ODI innings will be eclipsed for a long long time.

Crickbuzz Commentary: 
Think of the greatest warriors in the history of humanity. Think Alexander, think Genghis Khan, think Julius Caesar and today you can add another great contemporary warrior to that list. His name is Glenn Maxwell. An innings that defied logic, that tested the limits of human capabilities as Glenn Maxwell on one leg, with a semi-functional back took Australia from the dooms of defeat to the whims of victory. Functioning purely on adrenaline, the Big Show has today become an immortal in the world of cricket.
